{"name":"ping","description":"ping","usage":"ping [options] <destination>","options":[{"names":["-a"],"argument":"","description":"use audible ping"},{"names":["-A"],"argument":"","description":"use adaptive ping"},{"names":["-B"],"argument":"","description":"sticky source address"},{"names":["-c"],"argument":"<count>","description":"stop after <count> replies"},{"names":["-D"],"argument":"","description":"print timestamps"},{"names":["-d"],"argument":"","description":"use SO_DEBUG socket option"},{"names":["-f"],"argument":"","description":"flood ping"},{"names":["-h"],"argument":"","description":"print help and exit"},{"names":["-I"],"argument":"<interface>","description":"either interface name or address"},{"names":["-i"],"argument":"<interval>","description":"seconds between sending each packet"},{"names":["-L"],"argument":"","description":"suppress loopback of multicast packets"},{"names":["-l"],"argument":"<preload>","description":"send <preload> number of packages while waiting replies"},{"names":["-m"],"argument":"<mark>","description":"tag the packets going out"},{"names":["-M"],"argument":"<pmtud opt>","description":"define mtu discovery, can be one of <do|dont|want>"},{"names":["-n"],"argument":"","description":"no dns name resolution"},{"names":["-O"],"argument":"","description":"report outstanding replies"},{"names":["-p"],"argument":"<pattern>","description":"contents of padding byte"},{"names":["-q"],"argument":"","description":"quiet output"},{"names":["-Q"],"argument":"<tclass>","description":"use quality of service <tclass> bits"},{"names":["-s"],"argument":"<size>","description":"use <size> as number of data bytes to be sent"},{"names":["-S"],"argument":"<size>","description":"use <size> as SO_SNDBUF socket option value"},{"names":["-t"],"argument":"<ttl>","description":"define time to live"},{"names":["-U"],"argument":"","description":"print user-to-user latency"},{"names":["-v"],"argument":"","description":"verbose output"},{"names":["-V"],"argument":"","description":"print version and exit"},{"names":["-w"],"argument":"<deadline>","description":"reply wait <deadline> in seconds"},{"names":["-W"],"argument":"<timeout>","description":"time to wait for response"},{"names":["-4"],"argument":"","description":"use IPv4"},{"names":["-b"],"argument":"","description":"allow pinging broadcast"},{"names":["-R"],"argument":"","description":"record route"},{"names":["-T"],"argument":"<timestamp>","description":"define timestamp, can be one of <tsonly|tsandaddr|tsprespec>"},{"names":["-6"],"argument":"","description":"use IPv6"},{"names":["-F"],"argument":"<flowlabel>","description":"define flow label, default is random"},{"names":["-N"],"argument":"<nodeinfo opt>","description":"use icmp6 node info query, try <help> as argument"}],"tldr":"> Send ICMP ECHO_REQUEST packets to network hosts.\n> More information: <https://manned.org/ping>.\n\n- Ping host:\n\n`ping {{host}}`\n\n- Ping a host only a specific number of times:\n\n`ping -c {{count}} {{host}}`\n\n- Ping host, specifying the interval in seconds between requests (default is 1 second):\n\n`ping -i {{seconds}} {{host}}`\n\n- Ping host without trying to lookup symbolic names for addresses:\n\n`ping -n {{host}}`\n\n- Ping host and ring the bell when a packet is received (if your terminal supports it):\n\n`ping -a {{host}}`\n\n- Also display a message if no response was received:\n\n`ping -O {{host}}`\n"}
